- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper discusses the computational aspects of solving the OPF problem using different convex relaxations, which falls under the domain of numerical analysis. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper involves the application of computational techniques to solve an engineering problem, specifically the optimal control of power flow in electrical networks.
